{
  "title": "Flux Revision + PolicyReports (which version, where, passing?)",
  "uid": "flux-policy-version",
  "tags": ["policy-as-versioned-flux"],
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "editable": true,
  "time": {"from": "now-6h", "to": "now"},
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "cluster",
        "type": "custom",
        "label": "cluster",
        "query": "cluster1",
        "current": {"text": "cluster1", "value": "cluster1"},
        "options": [{"text": "cluster1", "value": "cluster1", "selected": true}],
        "description": "One Prometheus per cluster today (issue 15) -- a real cross-cluster query (Thanos/federation, or a per-cluster Grafana datasource this variable picks between) is issue 10's design question once cluster2 exists, not answered here."
      },
      {
        "name": "policy_version",
        "type": "query",
        "label": "policy-version",
        "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"},
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(gotk_resource_info{customresource_kind=\"GitRepository\", name=~\"policy-.*\"}, name)",
          "refId": "PolicyVersionVariable"
        },
        "regex": "/^policy-(?<text>.*)$/",
        "refresh": 2,
        "includeAll": true,
        "multi": false,
        "current": {"text": "All", "value": "$__all"}
      },
      {
        "name": "DS_PROMETHEUS",
        "type": "datasource",
        "label": "Prometheus",
        "query": "prometheus",
        "current": {}
      },
      {
        "name": "DS_INFINITY",
        "type": "datasource",
        "label": "Infinity",
        "query": "yesoreyeram-infinity-datasource",
        "current": {}
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Which version, where? (Flux GitRepository + Kustomization revisions)",
      "type": "table",
      "gridPos": {"h": 9, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0},
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "gotk_resource_info{customresource_kind=~\"GitRepository|Kustomization\", name=~\".*$policy_version.*\"}",
          "format": "table",
          "instant": true,
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "includeByName": {
              "customresource_kind": true,
              "name": true,
              "revision": true,
              "ready": true,
              "source_name": true
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "title": "Is it actually passing? (PolicyReport results for $policy_version)",
      "type": "barchart",
      "gridPos": {"h": 9, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 9},
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum by (status) (policy_report_result{policy=~\".*$policy_version\"})",
          "legendFormat": "{{status}}",
          "instant": true,
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "title": "Are controls satisfied? (issue 21 -- OSCAL assessment-results, cloud plane, live from the C2P CronJob)",
      "description": "Empty table = every mapped NIST control (sc-28, cp-10) is currently satisfied. A row here names a control that is NOT satisfied right now, sourced from the real, live cluster's PolicyReports every 15 minutes (infrastructure/c2p/) -- not a spike.",
      "type": "table",
      "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 18},
      "datasource": {"type": "yesoreyeram-infinity-datasource", "uid": "${DS_INFINITY}"},
      "targets": [
        {
          "type": "json",
          "source": "url",
          "format": "table",
          "url": "http://oscal-file-server.monitoring.svc.cluster.local/assessment-results.json",
          "url_options": {"method": "GET"},
          "root_selector": "assessment-results.results[0].findings",
          "columns": [
            {"selector": "target.target-id", "text": "control", "type": "string"},
            {"selector": "target.status.state", "text": "state", "type": "string"},
            {"selector": "target.status.reason", "text": "reason", "type": "string"}
          ],
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "title": "Adoption velocity (issue 21 -- Renovate PR state on this fleet repo, live from GitHub's public API)",
      "description": "Real PRs opened/merged against this repo -- the same bump PRs issue 11's Renovate customManager opens. Not the literal 'github' Grafana plugin (would need a provisioned GitHub token) -- infinity querying GitHub's public REST API unauthenticated, same first-party-datasource / no-bespoke-exporter outcome, documented honestly.",
      "type": "table",
      "gridPos": {"h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 26},
      "datasource": {"type": "yesoreyeram-infinity-datasource", "uid": "${DS_INFINITY}"},
      "targets": [
        {
          "type": "json",
          "source": "url",
          "format": "table",
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/policy-as-versioned-flux/fleet/pulls?state=all&per_page=20&sort=created&direction=desc",
          "url_options": {"method": "GET"},
          "root_selector": "",
          "columns": [
            {"selector": "number", "text": "PR", "type": "number"},
            {"selector": "title", "text": "title", "type": "string"},
            {"selector": "state", "text": "state", "type": "string"},
            {"selector": "merged_at", "text": "merged_at", "type": "timestamp"},
            {"selector": "created_at", "text": "created_at", "type": "timestamp"}
          ],
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
